{"lemma":"أَمْرِئَةٍ","slug":"أَمْرِئَةٍ","root":"م.ر.#","root_slug":"م-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38396","n14354"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A6%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oesophagus"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ma.riːʔ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38396","headword_ar":"مَرِىْءٌ","root":"mrA'","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"œsophagus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gullet"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a slaughtered camel, or sheep or goat, (S,) and of a man, (Zj, in his Khalk el-Insán,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canal through which the food and drink pass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head of the stomach;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contiguous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adherent"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huloquwm","text_ar":"حُلْقُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"windpipe"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through which the food and drink pass, and by which they enter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoriy^apN","text_ar":"اَمْرِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muruw^N","text_ar":"مُرُوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) It is also written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mariY~N","text_ar":"مَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^otiynA fiY mivoli mariYo'i Aln~aEaAmi","text_ar":"يَاْتِينا فِى مِثْلِ مَرِىْءِ النَّعَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It comes to us as it were through the gullet of the ostrich"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a proverbial expression, from a trad., alluding to paucity of food; the ostrich being particularized because of the slenderness of its neck, whence is inferred the narrowness of its gullet. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wholesome, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maruw^a","text_ar":"مَرُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haniyoy^FA mariyoy^FA","text_ar":"هَنِيْيًا مَرِيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hnA^","text_ar":"هنا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and see 1 in the present art. ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayovN mariYo'N","text_ar":"غَيْثٌ مَرِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rain productive of good result"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaA^N mariYo'N","text_ar":"كَلَاٌ مَرِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wholesome herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN mariyoy^apN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ مَرِيْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land salubrious in its air."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mariYo'N","text_ar":"مَرِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Manly, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maruw^a","text_ar":"مَرُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n14354","headword_ar":"مُرْىءٍ","root":"rA^Y","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a she-camel, and a ewe or she-goat, (M,) and any female in a state of pregnancy, except a solid-hoofed animal and a beast of prey,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whose udder shows her to be pregnant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muroy^iyapN","text_ar":"مُرْيِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) and in like manner applied to a woman: (M:) or, applied to a ewe or she-goat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"big in her udder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}